HEADWORD: Fluxional
<hw>Flux"ion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
having the nature of, fluxion or fluxions; variable;
inconstant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> The merely human,the temporary and <qex>fluxional</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fluxional structure</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>,
<cd>fluidal structure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fluxionary</ent>⟦br⟧
